            <section>
               <title value="Hospital course note"/>
               <code>
                  <coding>
                     <system value="http://loinc.org"/>
                     <code value="8648-8"/>
                     <display value="Hospital course note"/>
                  </coding>
               </code>
               <text>
                  <status value="generated"/>
                  <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding your patient, a 62-year-old female who was admitted on 25 September 1996 at her own request for voluntary surgical sterilization. Prior to the procedure, a thorough preoperative assessment was performed, including clinical examination, routine laboratory workup, and anaesthetic evaluation, all of which returned satisfactory results. The patient confirmed her informed consent following detailed counselling regarding the permanent nature of the procedure. On 25 September 1996, bilateral tubal ligation was performed laparoscopically under general anaesthesia without intraoperative or postoperative complications. Recovery was uneventful and the patient was discharged home on 26 September 1996 in good general condition. No further gynaecological follow-up is required unless the patient presents with concerns. Please continue routine primary care management. Yours sincerely.</div>
               </text>
            </section>
